body:
@apaszke or @soumith 

I feel like the `.to` method in `0.4.0` is sufficient functionality for core pytorch. I still think my `XPU` class is useful --- because it can abstract `DataParallel` --- but it no longer provides functionality that the core library is sorely missing. 

That being said, I'm closing this PR, but I'm going to continue to maintain `XPU` in my external [`netharn`](https://github.com/Erotemic/netharn/) library, which is built on top of pytorch and provides a training harness and hyperparameter tracking.
